This paper deals with the problem of remote Operating System detection, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes the use of neural networks to improve classical techniques, which involves the use of statistical and machine learning tools (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the topology and inner workings of the neural networks used, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of Nmap signatures, which is a tool commonly used in computer vision and image processing (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the fine-tuning of parameters, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
